          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Gross rental yield is calculated by dividing annual rental income by the property purchase price, without deducting any expenses. Net rental yield subtracts operating expenses such as property taxes, insurance, maintenance, management fees, and vacancy losses from the rental income before dividing by the property price. Net yield gives a more accurate picture of actual investment returns.",
